'''Association Sportive Taiarapu Football Club''', is a [[association football|football]] club from [[Taiarapu-Ouest]], [[Tahiti]]. It currently competes at [[Tahiti Ligue 1]]. It merged from the fusion of two previous teams, the [[AS Vairao]] and the [[AS Roniu]]<ref>[https://taiarapu-fc.kalisport.com/presentation], Taiarapu FC</ref>. 

On 23 February 2018, Taiarapu player Mickaël Tetuanui suffered a cardiac arrest and passed away during a match of [[Tahiti Cup]] in [[Teahupoo]]<ref>[https://www.oceaniafootball.com/ofc-joins-tahiti-football-in-mourning/], Oceania Football Confederation</ref>.

