{{Infobox football biography | name = Armand Forcherio | image = | fullname = Armand Forcherio | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1941|3|1|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Monaco]] | currentclub = | position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 1961–1972 | clubs1 = [[AS Monaco|Monaco]] | caps1 = 248 | goals1 = 2 | nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = | manageryears1 = 1972–1974 | manageryears2 = 1976–1977 | managerclubs1 = [[AC Arles-Avignon|Arles-Avignon]] | managerclubs2 = [[AS Monaco|Monaco]] }} '''Armand Forcherio''' (born 1 March 1941) is a former Monégasque footballer, who played as a defender for [[AS Monaco FC|AS Monaco]] from 1961 to 1972. He then managed the same team from 1976 to 1977, the only Monégasque to manage the club. He also played for French club AC Arles-Avignon.
