#REDIRECT [[Jorge Hernán "Cuty" Monge]]{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Estadio Jorge "Cuty" Monge | nickname = | image = | fullname = Estadio Jorge "Cuty" Monge | location = [[Desamparados Canton|Desamparados]], [[Costa Rica]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = | built = | opened = | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Desamparados Canton]] | operator = | surface = Artificial | dimensions = 105 x 75 m | construction_cost = | architect = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor= | project_manager = | main_contractors = | former_names = | tenants = [[Orión F.C.|Orión]] | seating_capacity = 5,500 | }}
'''Estadio Jorge "Cuty" Monge''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Desamparados Canton|Desamparados]], [[Costa Rica]].
It has been used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches, on club level by [[Brujas F.C.|Brujas]] of the [[Primera División de Costa Rica]] when they moved there from [[Escazú]] in 2007.<ref>[http://wvw.nacion.com/ln_ee/2007/julio/09/ultima-sr1162116.html Brujas a Desamparados] - Nación {{es|icon}}</ref> The stadium has a capacity of 5,500 spectators<ref>https://int.soccerway.com/national/costa-rica/primera-division/2010-2011/torneo-de-verano/venues/</ref> and was named after former Costa Rica international striker [[Jorge Hernán Monge]].
