{{refimprove|date=November 2017}} {{distinguish|text=[[Shenzhen F.C.|Shenzhen Xiangxue Eisiti]], its parent club}} {{for|full list of football club that was sponsored by Xiangxue|Xiangxue (disambiguation)}} {{Infobox football club | clubname = Xiangxue Eisiti | image = | fullname = | nickname = | founded = 2008 | dissolved = 2009 | ground = Hong Kong (no fixed location) | owntitle = Parent club | owner = [[Shenzhen F.C.|Shenzhen Xiangxue Eisiti F.C.]] | capacity = | chairman = | mgrtitle = | manager = | league = [[Hong Kong First Division League]] | season = [[Hong Kong First Division League 2008–09|2008–09]] | position = First Division, 13th (relegated) | pattern_la1=|pattern_b1=|pattern_ra1= | leftarm1=|body1=|rightarm1=|shorts1=|socks1= | pattern_la2=|pattern_b2=|pattern_ra2= | leftarm2=|body2=|rightarm2=|shorts2=|socks2= }} {{Chinese|t=香雪上清飲|s=香雪上清饮|p=Xiāng xuě shàng qīng yǐn|j=hoeng1 syut3 soeng5 cing1 jam2|order=ts|showflag=pj}} '''Shenzhen F.C. II''', known as '''[[Xiangxue Pharmaceutical|Xiangxue]] Eisiti''' for sponsorship reason, was a [[China|Chinese]] football team which played in [[Hong Kong First Division League]] in 2008–09 season. It was the [[reserve team]] of [[Shenzhen F.C.]], known as Shenzhen Xiangxue Eisiti (''Shenzhen Xiangxue Shangqingyin'') for sponsorship reasons at that time.
==Home ground== Xiangxue Eisiti wanted to host its games at the sports ground of {{ill|Shenzhen Bogang F.C.|zh|深圳壆岗足球俱乐部}} in [[Shajing Subdistrict, Shenzhen|Shajing]], [[Bao'an District]], but after inspection by the HKFA, the ground was considered unsuitable to host any league games.<ref>{{Cite press release|url=http://www.hkfa.com/includes_files/board_details.php?news_id=6083 |script-title=zh:2008/09年度香港足球總會快意空調甲組聯賽安排 |access-date=2008-09-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080912233706/http://www.hkfa.com/includes_files/board_details.php?news_id=6083 |archive-date=2008-09-12 |dead-url=yes |df=|publisher=HKFA|language=zh-hk }}</ref> Instead, Xiangxue Eisiti had to play all their home games at [[Mongkok Stadium]] or [[Siu Sai Wan Sports Ground]].
